So we could conclude that to configure access to my managed nodes, I need to generate an SSH key:

ssh-keygen

then copy that key to my managed hosts;

ssh-copy-id -i /home/user/.ssh/id_rsa.pub user@hostnameOrIP 

once connected, verify that with that user I can become root without a password so that become works

sudo -i or add a file in /etc/sudoers.d/user with 'user ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL'

remember that details about how to configure sudoers files can be found in 'man sudoers' and search for 'wheel' keyword.

